and he shows he is tempted by switching from the formal &quot;ye&quot; to the
intimate &quot;thou.&quot; But then the contrary mode appeared, of sarcastically
using the formal/superior plural to insult an uppity child or servant.

By Modern English proper everybody essentially said &quot;to hell with it&quot; and
used &quot;you&quot; for everything.

